            <br>
			Greetings all,<br><br>first I would like to say I am sorry for the downtime, but I had to "resync" some database stuff and do alot of uploading to the site.<br><br>Though most of the changes arnt really visible to you guys (code/database cleanups etc) I do have a list of the new features and bug fixes with this update:<br><br><b>Bug Fixes:</b><br><i>- Fixed a bug in <b>change member info</b> where some names where missing from the primary character list.<br>- Fixed the bug in the <b>send pop-up note</b> which were showing way to many names.<br>- Fixed the bug that caused you to be forced to type in your email when going into <b>change member info</b>. Its not a mandatory field anymore.</i><br><br><b>New Features:</b><br><i>- Added <b>views</b> to the message boards so its now possible to see how many that have viewed any topics from this day and forth.<br>- Its now possible to add your own <b>signature</b> to your created messages. This is done by editing the <b>signature</b> field in your member info.<br>- Your IP-Address will now be "registret" along with your messages, so we can track you down if you spam us ;)<br>- Along with the IP-addresses its now possible to be "partial" banned from our site, meaning you will be restricted to a "view-only" view of our message boards.<br>- Poll can now be created as "guild only" or "all". If "guild only" polls are made you are only able to vote once and only if you login and then go to the <b>current news</b> to vote or the poll will only show the result for you (and always for other non-members). If the poll is created as "all" it works just as it has always done with the possible "cheating" feature.<br>- Wrong login tries on your member account will now be registret (with the IP-address) and info about this given to you when you login.<br>- A new feature has been added to the member section called, <b>Strategy menu</b>. This will give you access to a new menu containing a list of zone strategies (empty at the moment but strategies will hopefully be added later).<br></i><br><br>Well, I think that about covers the visible part for most of you... I might have forgotten something and I might also have created new errors along with all these changes - so please bear with me and tell me about any new/old errors you detect.
